IDENTITY: s0(k) = C(2k+1,k) = (2k+1)/(k+1) · C(2k,k)

So: s0 = (2k+1)·C_k (where C_k = Catalan number)
    s2 = C(2k+2,k+1) = C(2(k+1), k+1) = central binomial (shifted)
